Package: panelcert
Type: Package
Title: Inference-Adequacy Diagnostics for Panel-Data Designs
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: person("Stanislaw M. S.", "Halkiewicz", email = "smsh@duck.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0000-7344-7522"))
Description: Certifies whether naive inference on an already-estimated
    fixed-effect panel design is size-controlled, and if not, by how much.
    Three diagnostic modules, one per source paper: leverage/variance
    estimator adequacy (HC0-HC3 hierarchy under fixed-effect saturation),
    measurement-error adequacy (Stock-Yogo-style within-reliability
    thresholds via exact inversion of the non-central size), and
    staggered-DiD TWFE-heterogeneity adequacy (the Gamma design statistic
    and its cluster-robust form). Diagnostic only: consumes fitted output,
    implements no remedies, and points to them.
